          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The forward scattering cross section at theta",
                " about 1.0 and 1.7 degree of E = 4 - 10 MeV",
                " monoenergetic photons from Pb and Bi targets has",
                " been measured. The photon beam was obtained from",
                " Fe(n,gamma) reaction. The elastic cross section at",
                " such angles, being dominated by Rayleigh and",
                " Delbruck scattering processes, was measured",
                " relative to the Compton cross section. The fact",
                " that one of the gamma-lines of Fe(n,gamma) reaction",
                " happens to overlap the 7.28 MeV level in 208Pb,",
                " yielding a strong nuclear resonance fluorescence",
                " signal, enabled to observe, for the first time,",
                " an interference effect with the scattering",
                " amplitude for the specific case of the random",
                " photoexcitation process is derived. The",
                " interference effect of this latter process with",
                " Rayleigh and Delbruck scattering was calculated",
                " and an excellent agreement with measured values",
                " was obtained."
              ]
            }
          ],
